00:21:01.042 --> 00:21:02.446
of some kind or another.

517
00:21:02.446 --> 00:21:04.277
Something's going down and, you know,

518
00:21:04.277 --> 00:21:05.923
watch out or you're going to get cancer

519
00:21:05.923 --> 00:21:07.223
and so on and so forth.

520
00:21:07.223 --> 00:21:11.298
So you, from a mechanistic model,

521
00:21:11.298 --> 00:21:12.993
you have a subconscious mind

522
00:21:12.993 --> 00:21:15.931
and even a mind filled with this negative programming.

523
00:21:15.931 --> 00:21:19.832
You have to override it so to speak

524
00:21:19.832 --> 00:21:24.273
through constant positive focus.

525
00:21:24.273 --> 00:21:27.138
<v ->Yeah, I used to think you had to</v>

526
00:21:27.138 --> 00:21:30.342
have a positive focus 51 percent of the time.

527
00:21:30.342 --> 00:21:32.652
I wrote a book, A Visionary Life,

528
00:21:32.652 --> 00:21:34.986
and even put that in there.

529
00:21:34.986 --> 00:21:38.515
Then I heard the wonderful analogy of a plane.

530
00:21:38.515 --> 00:21:41.824
It's not an analogy, it's reality.

531
00:21:41.824 --> 00:21:46.389
A plane is off course 95 percent of it's time or more,

532
00:21:46.389 --> 00:21:49.768
but the pilot keeps correcting over and over and over.

533
00:21:49.768 --> 00:21:53.100
When I heard that I said, yes that's the story of my life.

534
00:21:53.100 --> 00:21:56.301
You can be off course, you can be in fear even,

535
00:21:56.301 --> 00:21:59.192
95 percent of the time or more.

536
00:21:59.192 --> 00:22:02.707
But if you keep getting back,

537
00:22:02.707 --> 00:22:05.249
you keep correcting, you keep remembering your dream

538
00:22:05.249 --> 00:22:08.616
and taking whatever little baby steps you can

539
00:22:08.616 --> 00:22:12.053
this week toward it, you get back on course.

540
00:22:12.053 --> 00:22:14.218
You get off course again right away,

541
00:22:14.218 --> 00:22:16.029
oh more fear, oh this is so hard,

542
00:22:16.029 --> 00:22:19.524
oh life is a struggle, it's so hard to succeed.

543
00:22:19.524 --> 00:22:20.964
Okay, you're off course.

544
00:22:20.964 --> 00:22:22.217
Then you get back on.

545
00:22:22.217 --> 00:22:25.004
No, I have this dream, I'm going for it,

546
00:22:25.004 --> 00:22:26.896
I'm going to do this thing

547
00:22:26.896 --> 00:22:30.333
and I'm putting an hour a week in toward this.

548
00:22:30.333 --> 00:22:32.707
I'm taking this step, you're back on course.

549
00:22:32.707 --> 00:22:35.272
So you can be off course most of the time.

550
00:22:35.272 --> 00:22:37.432
You can be fearful most of the time.

551
00:22:37.432 --> 00:22:39.382
You can be totally neurotic.

552
00:22:39.382 --> 00:22:43.353
I had this sort of epiphany seeing Ross Perot on TV

553
00:22:43.353 --> 00:22:45.915
one time, the first time I ever saw him.

554
00:22:45.915 --> 00:22:49.956
I thought, he's a billionaire and the man is wacko.

555
00:22:50.746 --> 00:22:53.924
And I realized now that I've met a lot of rich people,

556
00:22:53.924 --> 00:22:55.758
rich people are just as neurotic.

557
00:22:55.758 --> 00:22:59.706
And many are just as fearful as poor people.

558
00:23:01.156 --> 00:23:03.601
They just have one thing going,

559
00:23:03.601 --> 00:23:06.108
they dare to dream something and go for it.

560
00:23:06.108 --> 00:23:09.278
You know, they have just as many fears and anxieties

561
00:23:09.278 --> 00:23:12.877
and problems, but they have that piece of it,

562
00:23:12.877 --> 00:23:15.349
that they keep moving toward a goal,

563
00:23:15.349 --> 00:23:17.253
they keep focused on a goal

564
00:23:17.253 --> 00:23:20.887
and at some point that dream

565
00:23:20.887 --> 00:23:24.323
gets to become even an intention.

566
00:23:24.323 --> 00:23:26.924
I am going to do this.

567
00:23:26.924 --> 00:23:28.700
Once it becomes an intention,

568
00:23:29.810 --> 00:23:31.629
all the fears and anxieties in the world

569
00:23:31.629 --> 00:23:33.034
won't stop an intention.

570
00:23:33.034 --> 00:23:34.841
<v Voiceover>Now you're getting into</v>

571
00:23:34.841 --> 00:23:38.139
some kind of deep cosmic soul purpose thinking now.

572
00:23:38.139 --> 00:23:42.040
There has to be then embedded in that seed of that passion,

573
00:23:42.040 --> 00:23:44.443
that love for what you want to do,

574
00:23:44.443 --> 00:23:46.614
something that is far more powerful

575
00:23:46.614 --> 00:23:48.414
than the force of fear.

576
00:23:48.414 --> 00:23:51.014
<v ->Yes, yes, ultimately</v>

577
00:23:51.014 --> 00:23:54.091
our love is far more powerful than fear.

578
00:23:54.091 --> 00:23:55.728
It literally is.

579
00:23:55.728 --> 00:23:57.423
It's higher in our bodies,

580
00:23:57.423 --> 00:24:00.523
our fear is centered low, real low.

581
00:24:00.523 --> 00:24:03.866
I mean in worst cases of extreme fear

582
00:24:03.866 --> 00:24:06.699
you can lose control of your sphincter muscle.

583
00:24:06.699 --> 00:24:09.428
That's where fear is centered, down low.

584
00:24:09.428 --> 00:24:12.368
Where love is in your heart, it's higher.

585
00:24:12.368 --> 00:24:14.214
Love transcends fear.

586
00:24:14.214 --> 00:24:16.640
And if you really do what you love to do,

587
00:24:16.640 --> 00:24:21.168
if you dare to dream, it always does involve love

588
00:24:21.168 --> 00:24:24.424
and in some ways serving others.

589
00:24:24.424 --> 00:24:27.718
I do think the greatest key, at least for me

590
00:24:27.718 --> 00:24:30.191
in my words, to the greatest secret of all,

591
00:24:30.191 --> 00:24:34.025
I think is to love and serve yourself and others.

592
00:24:34.915 --> 00:24:38.400
And keep that in mind, that will overcome fears.

593
00:24:38.400 --> 00:24:42.298
When the fears arise, they're petty, they're self centered,

594
00:24:42.298 --> 00:24:47.003
they're limiting, it's this little limited little me.

595
00:24:47.003 --> 00:24:49.907
Eckhart Tolle keeps talking about the little me.

596
00:24:49.907 --> 00:24:53.912
It's the little me saying, oh this is hard,

597
00:24:53.912 --> 00:24:56.254
this is hard, life is hard,

598
00:24:56.254 --> 00:24:57.891
you know, life is a struggle.

599
00:24:57.891 --> 00:24:59.249
It's so hard to make money,

600
00:24:59.249 --> 00:25:00.791
it's so hard to succeed.

601
00:25:00.791 --> 00:25:02.021
That's the little me.

602
00:25:02.021 --> 00:25:04.030
We're far greater than that.

603
00:25:04.030 --> 00:25:07.188
We're far greater, more creative people.

604
00:25:07.188 --> 00:25:10.764
We have just as much potential as anybody else.

605
00:25:10.764 --> 00:25:14.874
We all have this amazing, amazing physical body,

606
00:25:14.874 --> 00:25:19.076
this phenomenal brain, and this incredible connection

607
00:25:19.076 --> 00:25:22.545
to some vast subconscious or whatever you want to call it.

608
00:25:22.545 --> 00:25:25.111
Some people even just call it the universe.

609
00:25:25.111 --> 00:25:28.722
We have this great, deep connection

610
00:25:28.722 --> 00:25:31.821
that we can even

611
00:25:31.821 --> 00:25:34.085
summon into our lives.

612
00:25:34.085 --> 00:25:37.231
We can summon great power into our life

613
00:25:37.231 --> 00:25:39.030
by doing what we love.

614
00:25:39.030 --> 00:25:42.862
<v Voiceover>And you took a few practical steps</v>

615
00:25:42.862 --> 00:25:43.764
along the way.

616
00:25:43.764 --> 00:25:46.661
One you decided, okay, I have to take responsibility,

617
00:25:46.661 --> 00:25:48.972
I'm the boss I've been waiting for in my company

618
00:25:48.972 --> 00:25:51.055
which is failing right now. (laughs)

619
00:25:51.055 --> 00:25:52.501
<v ->Right, right, yes yes, right.</v>

620
00:25:52.501 --> 00:25:54.311
<v Voiceover>You became the boss, you started turning</v>

621
00:25:54.311 --> 00:25:57.110
it around, even within a year you started turning it around.

622
00:25:57.110 --> 00:25:58.816
And there were a few little kind of,

623
00:25:58.816 --> 00:26:01.545
I won't call them tricks, but tools that you use

624
00:26:01.545 --> 00:26:04.981
to be able to repattern this in yourself

625
00:26:04.981 --> 00:26:07.559
that you write about in The Greatest Secret of All.

626
00:26:07.559 --> 00:26:09.576
Can you share just a couple of these little

627
00:26:09.576 --> 00:26:12.293
functional things that you have people work with,

628
00:26:12.293 --> 00:26:13.253
that you work with.

629
00:26:13.253 --> 00:26:14.980
<v ->Yeah, to me,</v>

630
00:26:15.832 --> 00:26:18.129
maybe the most powerful thing of all

631
00:26:18.129 --> 00:26:20.938
is finding the right affirmation in the moment.

632
00:26:20.938 --> 00:26:23.199
Or just finding something in the moment

633
00:26:23.199 --> 00:26:25.173
that gets you back on course.

634
00:26:26.503 --> 00:26:29.415
Fortunately I wandered into this seminar when I was 28

635
00:26:29.415 --> 00:26:31.714
led by this man named Ken Keyes, Jr.

636
00:26:31.714 --> 00:26:33.177
who had written a book called

637
00:26:33.177 --> 00:26:35.914
Handbook to Higher Consciousness in the 70s.

638
00:26:35.914 --> 00:26:40.326
He understood something about our deep core beliefs

639
00:26:40.326 --> 00:26:43.794
and that's the piece of the pie that he really knew

640
00:26:43.794 --> 00:26:45.427
and could teach.

641
00:26:45.427 --> 00:26:49.398
And he taught us the core belief process he called it.

642
00:26:49.398 --> 00:26:52.161
And what it boils down to is

643
00:26:52.161 --> 00:26:55.238
realizing that all these beliefs

644
00:26:55.238 --> 00:26:58.477
that we've accepted as true in our lives,

645
00:26:58.477 --> 00:27:00.636
and certainly seem true in our lives,

646
00:27:00.636 --> 00:27:03.977
because we see them every day in our loves, they become...

647
00:27:03.977 --> 00:27:05.544
<v Voiceover>You see evidence.</v>

648
00:27:05.544 --> 00:27:06.920
<v ->We see evidence in our lives.</v>

649
00:27:07.770 --> 00:27:09.456
If you're struggling to pay the rent,

650
00:27:09.456 --> 00:27:12.683
well it's true, it's hard to pay the rent, it's a struggle.

651
00:27:12.683 --> 00:27:15.220
Yes, well, life is a struggle, it's hard.

652
00:27:15.220 --> 00:27:17.287
He showed us these beliefs are not

653
00:27:17.287 --> 00:27:19.223
necessarily true in themselves.

654
00:27:19.223 --> 00:27:22.932
There are many people with very different sets of beliefs.

655
00:27:22.932 --> 00:27:25.932
So the beliefs are not true in themselves.

656
00:27:25.932 --> 00:27:28.104
But they become true in our experience

657
00:27:28.104 --> 00:27:29.508
if we believe them.

658
00:27:29.508 --> 00:27:33.374
So it's very good to look at all our beliefs.

659
00:27:33.374 --> 00:27:37.849
Look, how do we really think the world is?

660
00:27:37.849 --> 00:27:39.715
Is the world a struggle?

661
00:27:39.715 --> 00:27:43.605
Is the world some place that's limited in some way,

662
00:27:43.605 --> 00:27:47.044
or scarcity? Is there scarcity in the world?

663
00:27:47.044 --> 00:27:49.052
Is there scarcity in our lives?

664
00:27:49.052 --> 00:27:51.522
Is it hard to succeed?

665
00:27:51.522 --> 00:27:53.693
If so, those are just beliefs.

666
00:27:53.693 --> 00:27:55.933
And we can change those beliefs.

667
00:27:55.933 --> 00:27:57.962
<v Voiceover>And you can see evidence to the contrary.</v>

668
00:27:57.962 --> 00:27:58.688
<v ->Yes.</v>

669
00:27:58.688 --> 00:27:59.539
<v Voiceover>Around.</v>

670
00:27:59.539 --> 00:28:01.164
<v ->And once we change the belief,</v>

671
00:28:01.164 --> 00:28:03.474
we see evidence to the contrary in our lives.

672
00:28:03.474 --> 00:28:06.208
So for me, when I hit my financial low,

673
00:28:06.208 --> 00:28:08.146
one of the best things I did,

674
00:28:08.146 --> 00:28:09.844
I've already said one of the best things,

675
00:28:09.844 --> 00:28:11.179
I just heard that phrase,

676
00:28:11.179 --> 00:28:14.279
within every adversity is an equal or greater benefit.

677
00:28:14.279 --> 00:28:16.212
That was key.

678
00:28:16.212 --> 00:28:20.124
The other best thing I did was the core belief process,

679
00:28:20.124 --> 00:28:23.247
I did a very effective one that changed my life.

680
00:28:23.247 --> 00:28:25.754
I was driving to the bank.

681
00:28:25.754 --> 00:28:28.367
I'd gotten another credit card sent to me.

682
00:28:28.367 --> 00:28:30.700
I had been living for years on

683
00:28:30.700 --> 00:28:32.999
getting more credit cards, getting cash advances

684
00:28:32.999 --> 00:28:35.530
and paying down the minimums of the other cards.

685
00:28:35.530 --> 00:28:37.039
<v Voiceover>A lot of people can relate.</v>

686
00:28:37.039 --> 00:28:38.069
<v ->Yeah, right.</v>

687
00:28:38.069 --> 00:28:41.866
And I realized I was, I had all this anxiety,

688
00:28:41.866 --> 00:28:43.880
my stomach was just churning

689
00:28:43.880 --> 00:28:45.220
as I was going to the bank.

690
00:28:45.220 --> 00:28:47.914
Oh, now I'm 65 thousand in credit card debt,

691
00:28:47.914 --> 00:28:50.921
okay, that was, I remember thinking that number,

692
00:28:50.921 --> 00:28:54.352
that was a pretty big number for me to grapple with.

693
00:28:54.352 --> 00:28:57.092
And I felt this anxiety, and then I remembered,

694
00:28:57.092 --> 00:28:59.658
oh this is the time to do the core belief process,

695
00:28:59.658 --> 00:29:01.329
when you feel anxiety.

696
00:29:01.329 --> 00:29:03.663
And I did, I went through these steps,

697
00:29:03.663 --> 00:29:08.091
all they are is asking you eight really simple questions.

698
00:29:08.091 --> 00:29:10.472
The first is, what is the problem?

699
00:29:10.472 --> 00:29:12.596
That we know, we know that.

700
00:29:12.596 --> 00:29:14.570
<v Voiceover>It's almost like you have to throw a bone</v>

701
00:29:14.570 --> 00:29:16.575
to that part of the mind that's trying to deal with,

702
00:29:16.575 --> 00:29:18.932
that's trying to create problems for yourself, right?

703
00:29:18.932 --> 00:29:20.455
Give it a bone.

704
00:29:20.455 --> 00:29:21.172
Acknowledge it.

705
00:29:21.172 --> 00:29:22.887
<v ->And really acknowledge the problem, right.</v>

706
00:29:22.887 --> 00:29:25.114
And that one we all know very quickly.

707
00:29:25.114 --> 00:29:27.389
We can say, oh it's so hard,

708
00:29:27.389 --> 00:29:29.560
it's so hard to succeed, it's hard to make money.

709
00:29:29.560 --> 00:29:31.854
For me it was, I'm almost bankrupt

710
00:29:31.854 --> 00:29:34.164
because I'm just an idiot with money, that's the problem.

711
00:29:34.164 --> 00:29:36.616
Then two, it's really good to ask,

712
00:29:36.616 --> 00:29:38.857
what are you feeling physically?

713
00:29:38.857 --> 00:29:41.806
And just tune in, ah, I realized

714
00:29:41.806 --> 00:29:43.335
my neck and shoulders were uptight,

715
00:29:43.335 --> 00:29:44.903
my stomach was churning.

716
00:29:44.903 --> 00:29:47.471
Three, what are you feeling emotionally?

717
00:29:47.471 --> 00:29:49.445
And just nail the emotion.

718
00:29:49.445 --> 00:29:52.712
Sometimes men especially will start going on and on and on

719
00:29:52.712 --> 00:29:55.414
getting philosophical, no, just nail the emotion.

720
00:29:55.414 --> 00:29:58.084
I feel anxiety.

721
00:29:58.084 --> 00:30:00.877
I feel there's some kind of guilt

722
00:30:00.877 --> 00:30:04.130
or sadness or, underneath it all

723
00:30:04.130 --> 00:30:06.127
there's always fear.

724
00:30:06.127 --> 00:30:07.065
There's always fear.

725
00:30:07.065 --> 00:30:09.128
Okay, you acknowledge that fear.

726
00:30:09.128 --> 00:30:11.160
I feel this fear.

727
00:30:11.160 --> 00:30:14.770
Then you just say,

728
00:30:14.770 --> 00:30:16.508
what tapes have I been running

729
00:30:16.508 --> 00:30:17.945
is what we used to say, or

730
00:30:17.945 --> 00:30:19.907
what's been going through my mind?

731
00:30:19.907 --> 00:30:22.341
What am I telling myself repeatedly?

732
00:30:22.341 --> 00:30:26.080
And you just out loud spill out all those thoughts.

733
00:30:26.080 --> 00:30:29.714
Well I'm just an idiot with money, I just can't handle it,

734
00:30:29.714 --> 00:30:30.944
it's just so hard.

735
00:30:30.944 --> 00:30:33.422
You just run all those things

736
00:30:33.422 --> 00:30:36.824
so you're consciously looking at them

737
00:30:36.824 --> 00:30:39.425
rather than being this passive victim

738
00:30:39.425 --> 00:30:41.802
of all these thoughts and feelings.

739
00:30:41.802 --> 00:30:45.772
Then, five, a very good thing to do is to say

740
00:30:45.772 --> 00:30:47.998
what's the worst that could happen?

741
00:30:47.998 --> 00:30:50.700
In this situation what's the worst thing that can happen?

742
00:30:50.700 --> 00:30:52.869
Well, I could go bankrupt.

743
00:30:53.769 --> 00:30:56.641
Then you say, what's the very worst thing that can happen?

744
00:30:56.641 --> 00:30:59.578
So you really look at your worst fears.

745
00:30:59.578 --> 00:31:02.016
We tend to want to hide our worst fears.

746
00:31:02.016 --> 00:31:03.479
We don't want to confront them.

747
00:31:03.479 --> 00:31:04.710
We're afraid of them.

748
00:31:05.710 --> 00:31:07.577
That little question force us to

749
00:31:07.577 --> 00:31:09.888
open all those closet doors and look,

750
00:31:09.888 --> 00:31:12.813
what are your worst deepest fears?

751
00:31:12.813 --> 00:31:14.892
What's behind all this anxiety?

752
00:31:14.892 --> 00:31:16.192
What is that fear?

753
00:31:16.192 --> 00:31:18.031
For me, what I got down to is,

754
00:31:18.801 --> 00:31:23.239
well I could die painfully and slowly

755
00:31:23.239 --> 00:31:26.777
a drunken bum in a gutter somewhere

756
00:31:26.777 --> 00:31:29.305
and no one would know or care.

757
00:31:29.305 --> 00:31:30.452
I would just lay there...

758
00:31:30.452 --> 00:31:32.045
<v Voiceover>Well you got to the bottom of it.</v>

759
00:31:32.045 --> 00:31:34.082
<v ->Yes, that was somewhere at the bottom.</v>

760
00:31:34.082 --> 00:31:37.322
And it usually brings up even some chuckles

761
00:31:37.322 --> 00:31:40.093
because you realize the chance of your worst fears

762
00:31:40.093 --> 00:31:43.286
coming true are very slim.

763
00:31:43.286 --> 00:31:46.020
Very very slim.

764
00:31:46.020 --> 00:31:47.889
Very remote.

765
00:31:47.889 --> 00:31:49.967
So then you say, okay, what's the best case

766
00:31:49.967 --> 00:31:53.299
in this scenario? What's the best thing that could happen?

767
00:31:54.419 --> 00:31:58.007
I've done this, over the years, hundreds of times now

768
00:31:58.007 --> 00:31:59.609
with hundreds of people.

769
00:31:59.609 --> 00:32:03.413
Inevitably we get into our worst fears

770
00:32:03.413 --> 00:32:07.372
with incredible energy and we get into it right away.

771
00:32:07.372 --> 00:32:09.485
Then you say, okay, in this situation

772
00:32:09.485 --> 00:32:10.855
what's the best that could happen?

773
00:32:10.855 --> 00:32:14.591
And we go, huh, hmm, let me think.

